Many countries can do it. Interpol cannot know for certain what is happening behind other boards. Even if it did know and approached China (for example), they would simply be told to get stuffed. Nobody would be allowed to come in and find evidence.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A> at: 5/22/02 7:34:33 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uyales.showPublicProfile?language=EN>yales</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MegaLipidCephaloid</span><br>  Posts: 342<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/22/02 8:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~yales/images/53invad2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~nsmessageboard/ezboard/posticons/fry1.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Orion themed arms race?</span><hr size=1> Production at above the levels of roughly 1 device is pretty easy to spot. It is rather straightforward to estimate production levels via either enrichment facilities or (even easier) reactor/reprocessing production.<br>
<br>
It is production of only one or two devices over a period of years that can be (sometimes) masked.<br>
<br>
Production of the required tons of fissiles for a single Orion type vehicle would be as obvious as a trout in the milk picture.<br>
<br>
Plus, each of the various energy level bomb would have to undergo a testing series to determine functionality and performance. This would also be straightforward detection.<br>
<br>
The required material (thousands of deuterium/tritium neutron generators, ultracapacitors, shaped charges, exploding foil detonators, etc.) would also be quite apparent.<br>
